OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FStrikes hamper police      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffighting crime - Met chief 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Public sector strikes could stop       
OL,6, officers fighting crime effectively,   
OL,7, the Metropolitan Police chief has said.
OL,9,FWriting in the Daily Telegraph, Sir    
OL,10,FMark Rowley says officers already spend
OL,11,F"too much time" on non-police work.    
OL,13,FThis includes spending hours in        
OL,14,Fhospitals dealing with people with     
OL,15,Fmental health conditions - which he    
OL,16,Fsays would worsen if strikes happen.   
OL,18,FSir Mark also writes that the Met needs
OL,19,Fa 27% budget increase "just to stand   
OL,20,Fstill" compared with 10 years ago.     
